but my mama was from Tennessee.

861
01:22:10,956 --> 01:22:13,516
Pete Garrison and I are having an affair.

862
01:22:16,795 --> 01:22:20,697
Please have a seat.
And... that's for you.

863
01:22:22,234 --> 01:22:24,998
You know, I don't know
all the evidence you have against him...

864
01:22:25,103 --> 01:22:28,300
but I do know why he failed
the lie detector test.

865
01:22:28,407 --> 01:22:33,538
And I know why he was
in that coffee shop looking for someone.

866
01:23:17,656 --> 01:23:21,649
Hello. U.S. Secret Service
up for the G8.

867
01:23:21,760 --> 01:23:24,320
I got a priority item
for the duty officer over at the lab.

868
01:23:24,429 --> 01:23:28,422
- That'll be that direction on the eighth floor.
- Thank you.

869
01:23:28,533 --> 01:23:31,024
Sign the log, please.

870
01:23:37,576 --> 01:23:41,512
I need any prints that
you can find off this cup.

871
01:23:41,613 --> 01:23:44,104
- Okay.
- Thank you very much.

872
01:23:46,351 --> 01:23:48,444
See you in about 12 minutes.

873
01:24:06,638 --> 01:24:09,198
<i>Sweeps two and three now complete.</i>

874
01:24:48,914 --> 01:24:51,382
I'm gonna be pushing
post in a few minutes...

875
01:24:51,483 --> 01:24:53,576
- but if you want to grab a coffee...
- Marin.

876
01:24:53,685 --> 01:24:57,246
- Hey, Jill. This is Pete.
- A lot of people are looking for you.

877
01:24:57,355 --> 01:24:59,823
I'm sure they are.

878
01:24:59,925 --> 01:25:02,086
- Did you find any prints at the apartment?
- No. Nothing.

879
01:25:02,194 --> 01:25:06,756
I did. You gotta help me out. If I e-mail
the prints to you, how long is it gonna take...

880
01:25:06,865 --> 01:25:09,527
to check them against the F.B.I.
And C.I.A. Databases?

881
01:25:09,634 --> 01:25:11,534
Five minutes after I receive 'em.

882
01:25:11,636 --> 01:25:15,265
I'll call you five minutes
after I send them. Bye.

883
01:25:15,373 --> 01:25:18,103
I've got a print in here.
Could somebody run it for me, please?

884
01:25:18,210 --> 01:25:21,043
- Yeah, I got it.
- Thank you.

885
01:25:46,438 --> 01:25:49,271
In my experience a guilty man
doesn't break into a police station...

886
01:25:49,374 --> 01:25:51,706
and check fingerprints
for a few hours.

887
01:25:51,810 --> 01:25:53,778
What do you think?

888
01:25:55,480 --> 01:25:59,473
My phone was only on
for five minutes.

889
01:25:59,584 --> 01:26:01,518
I was in the neighborhood.

890
01:26:01,620 --> 01:26:05,886
Dave, I can't explain about the bank account.
The other things I can explain.

891
01:26:05,991 --> 01:26:08,323
- I know about the affair.
- It wasn't with Cindy.

892
01:26:08,426 --> 01:26:11,554
Oh, I know. The first lady.

893
01:26:11,663 --> 01:26:14,564
She told me everything.
I know you're being framed.

894
01:26:14,666 --> 01:26:17,499
She showed me the blackmail photos.

895
01:26:20,672 --> 01:26:23,038
So where does that leave us?

896
01:26:23,141 --> 01:26:27,339
- We need to find this guy.
- Come here.

897
01:26:27,445 --> 01:26:29,572
Yeah.

898
01:26:29,681 --> 01:26:33,117
You really are an idiot,
you know that?

899
01:26:33,218 --> 01:26:37,655
- You honestly thought that
this wouldn't be uncovered?
- Dave, I love her.

900
01:26:37,756 --> 01:26:39,690
Well, that's practical.

901
01:26:39,791 --> 01:26:43,727
The prints belong
to Gennady Ivanov, former K.G. <i>B...</i>

902
01:26:43,828 --> 01:26:48,060
now works for the personal security service
for the president of Karjastan.

903
01:26:48,166 --> 01:26:50,600
I'm also showing confirmed intel
that this is the guy...

904
01:26:50,702 --> 01:26:53,034
<i>responsible for the Central Asian</i>
<i>pipeline attacks.</i>

905
01:26:53,138 --> 01:26:55,538
Confirmed intel on what,
Agent Marin?

906
01:26:55,640 --> 01:26:58,939
This is a classified conversation.
We'll be out of here in two minutes.

907
01:26:59,044 --> 01:27:01,706
- Yeah. Whatever.
- Thank you.

908
01:27:01,813 --> 01:27:05,044
These people have the financial
and intelligence resources to pull this off.

909
01:27:05,150 --> 01:27:07,812
All right, let's get going.

910
01:27:10,822 --> 01:27:12,722
We've still gotta find the mole.

911
01:27:12,824 --> 01:27:15,292
We polygraphed every agent
with access to the president.

912
01:27:15,393 --> 01:27:17,520
Yours was the only one
that showed deception.

913
01:27:17,629 --> 01:27:20,757
We need to figure out
how the real traitor passed the test.

914
01:27:20,865 --> 01:27:22,492
Montrose had the list.

915
01:27:25,236 --> 01:27:28,205
You know I never guaranteed you success.

916
01:27:28,306 --> 01:27:30,206
Security's tighter than it's ever been.

917
01:27:30,308 --> 01:27:34,108
Routes, modes of transport,
they're all random now.

918
01:27:34,212 --> 01:27:36,510
<i>Yeah, but not random</i>
<i>to you, William.</i>

919
01:27:36,615 --> 01:27:42,144
I mean, if you wanted him on that helicopter
at Camp David, you could have put him there.

920
01:27:44,022 --> 01:27:47,116
<i>Now, you've been playing us</i>
<i>since the beginning.</i>

921
01:27:47,225 --> 01:27:49,921
<i>All right. Fair enough.</i>

922
01:27:50,028 --> 01:27:52,861
That's not gonna work anymore.

923
01:27:52,964 --> 01:27:56,263
- You did make a deal.
- Yeah.

924
01:27:56,368 --> 01:27:59,337
Twenty years ago with the K.G.B.,
which doesn't even exist anymore.

925
01:27:59,437 --> 01:28:01,997
Do you want out, William?

926
01:28:08,213 --> 01:28:11,478
Then give me... the president.

927
01:28:11,583 --> 01:28:13,676
<i>Just like you agreed.</i>

928
01:28:13,785 --> 01:28:15,753
No.

929
01:28:17,889 --> 01:28:19,857
I don't care.

930
01:28:20,992 --> 01:28:22,983
Expose me.

931
01:28:23,094 --> 01:28:26,928
I don't care if I spend the rest
of my life in prison for treason.

932
01:28:27,032 --> 01:28:29,626
I don't care if you kill me.

933
01:28:32,303 --> 01:28:35,864
- Here you go.
- Have a pint.

934
01:28:39,911 --> 01:28:42,709
Oh. Thank you.

935
01:28:44,049 --> 01:28:47,485
William...

936
01:28:47,585 --> 01:28:50,554
if you don't do this,
we're not gonna kill you.

937
01:28:58,463 --> 01:29:01,227
We are going to kill her.

938
01:29:05,303 --> 01:29:07,567
And we're gonna kill her.

939
01:29:09,607 --> 01:29:11,575
And then we're gonna kill her.

940
01:29:22,387 --> 01:29:25,379
<i>Yes, William, the K.G.B. 's gone.</i>

941
01:29:25,490 --> 01:29:27,958
<i>But we're still here.</i>

942
01:29:30,795 --> 01:29:33,355
<i>William, it's all right.</i>

943
01:29:33,465 --> 01:29:36,025
You do have a way out.

944
01:29:36,134 --> 01:29:38,102
But only one.

945
01:29:45,543 --> 01:29:48,569
When he finishes his speech,
you take him on the primary route...

946
01:29:48,680 --> 01:29:51,376
to the "B" motorcade
under the plaza...

947
01:29:51,483 --> 01:29:53,815
and you take the radios out.

948
01:29:55,687 --> 01:29:59,487
Then that's it.
And we'll do the rest.

949
01:30:02,393 --> 01:30:04,554
Hey, look.

950
01:30:07,966 --> 01:30:09,991
You can keep those.

951
01:30:10,101 --> 01:30:12,296
I got doubles.

952
01:30:19,844 --> 01:30:23,837
Jill, it's David. I want you to get
in touch with Downing and Medina.

953
01:30:23,948 --> 01:30:27,748
Confirm for me which one did
Montrose's polygraph and get back to me.

954
01:30:27,852 --> 01:30:31,413
- <i>We're on our way to city hall.</i>
- <i>Got it.</i>

955
01:30:38,763 --> 01:30:41,425
<i>Command Post from Apache follow-up.</i>

956
01:30:41,533 --> 01:30:44,093
<i>Arrive Martinez location</i>
<i>1740 hours. Copy.</i>

957
01:30:44,202 --> 01:30:46,932
<i>Summon security, DiPaola.</i>
<i>Cincinnati's moving to hold.</i>

958
01:30:47,038 --> 01:30:49,802
<i>All posts, all posts, be advised.</i>
<i>We have an arrival.</i>

959
01:30:49,908 --> 01:30:53,810
<i>Only essential traffic at this time.</i>

960
01:30:58,650 --> 01:31:01,050
- Everybody ready?
- Yes, sir.

961
01:31:01,152 --> 01:31:04,121
Let's do this.

962
01:31:04,222 --> 01:31:06,520
- Yeah, tell me what you got.

963
01:31:06,624 --> 01:31:10,560
- Montrose didn't take the polygraph.
- You're 100% sure?

964
01:31:10,662 --> 01:31:14,860
Positive. Polygraphers have no record
of Montrose even being tested.

965
01:31:14,966 --> 01:31:17,628
- Neither one of them.
- Montrose didn't take the polygraph.

966
01:31:26,077 --> 01:31:29,478
Now let there be no mistake.
In an uncertain and an unsafe world...

967
01:31:29,581 --> 01:31:31,879
America must be strong.

968
01:31:31,983 --> 01:31:33,883
But previous administrations...

969
01:31:33,985 --> 01:31:36,453
I also hacked into
Merriweather's staff mail.

970
01:31:36,554 --> 01:31:39,045
He was streaming
someone's offshore phone logs.

971
01:31:39,157 --> 01:31:41,648
- The logs are Montrose's.
- Give me the phone.

972
01:31:41,759 --> 01:31:43,590
Hi, Jill. It's Pete.

973
01:31:43,695 --> 01:31:47,222
Get a hold of the first lady and tell her...
only her... that it's Montrose.

974
01:31:47,332 --> 01:31:49,823
Got it.

975
01:31:49,934 --> 01:31:53,529
Jesus Christ, Pete. The first lady?
What were you thinkin'?

976
01:31:53,638 --> 01:31:56,937
I never saw it coming, Dave.

977
01:32:27,071 --> 01:32:31,872
<i>Be advised, they just allowed</i>
<i>two armed credentialed...</i>

978
01:32:31,976 --> 01:32:34,308
<i>American agents into the three perimeter</i>
<i>from checkpoint 386.</i>

979
01:32:34,412 --> 01:32:38,405
<i>Be advised, suspect Garrison</i>
<i>has just been let through...</i>

980
01:32:38,516 --> 01:32:40,575
I've got a scope on subject Garrison.

981
01:32:40,685 --> 01:32:42,585
<i>Ah, Jesus! I got Garrison</i>
<i>through the three.</i>

982
01:32:42,687 --> 01:32:46,453
<i>This resolution cannot</i>
<i>function alone. It is designed...</i>

983
01:32:46,557 --> 01:32:49,651
It's Garrison and Breck.

984
01:32:49,761 --> 01:32:52,491
Holster your weapons.
Holster your weapons!

985
01:32:52,597 --> 01:32:56,158
<i>I'm Agent Breckinridge.</i>
<i>I issued the warrant on Pete Garrison.</i>

986
01:32:56,267 --> 01:32:58,565
Subject in my sight.
Do I take the shot?

987
01:32:58,670 --> 01:33:02,299
<i>We must ratify the Kyoto Protocol.</i>

988
01:33:02,407 --> 01:33:06,810
- We must embrace the ideal
of an African economic union.
- Need assistance, over.

989
01:33:09,414 --> 01:33:12,144
- He's a Do Not Admit.
- We have orders.

990
01:33:12,250 --> 01:33:14,411
- I am countermanding your orders!
- You don't control this site.

991
01:33:14,519 --> 01:33:16,077
- Montrose does.
- Don't call him!

992
01:33:16,187 --> 01:33:18,087
- Montrose is the mole!
- Montrose?

993
01:33:18,189 --> 01:33:20,384
What's the procedure for that?

994
01:33:22,727 --> 01:33:25,696
<i>No unauthorized personnel</i>
<i>beyond the two perimeter.</i>

995
01:33:25,797 --> 01:33:27,765
Ma'am.

996
01:33:30,468 --> 01:33:33,028
Something's wrong.
My radio just went dead.

997
01:33:33,137 --> 01:33:35,435
I've lost my radio.
I don't have any radio.

998
01:33:35,540 --> 01:33:37,770
- <i>I'm not hearing any chatter.</i>
- I've got silence on all channels.

999
01:33:37,875 --> 01:33:40,537
- It's going down!
- Agent Garrison called on my line.

1000
01:33:40,645 --> 01:33:43,944
He wanted me to tell you
that Montrose is the mole.

1001
01:33:46,017 --> 01:33:50,613
<i>But I strongly believe that we can</i>
<i>protect our vital interests...</i>

1002
01:33:50,722 --> 01:33:53,316
<i>without causing resentment.</i>

1003
01:33:53,424 --> 01:33:56,120
- Get your hands in the air!

1004
01:33:56,227 --> 01:33:59,788
- Put that down!
- Pete Garrison is not the mole!

1005
01:33:59,897 --> 01:34:02,491
- <i>You are a Do Not Admit!</i>
- But at the same time...

1006
01:34:02,600 --> 01:34:06,001
- Mr. President.
- <i>Listen to me!</i>

1007
01:34:06,104 --> 01:34:08,834
<i>Do not let him</i>
<i>move the president!</i>

1008
01:34:08,940 --> 01:34:10,908
This way, Mr. President.

1009
01:34:11,009 --> 01:34:13,739
- Do not let Montrose move the president!
- Montrose, he's getting away!

1010
01:34:13,845 --> 01:34:16,712
Crystal. Crystal is the password.

1011
01:34:19,917 --> 01:34:22,715
We need your help.
Tom, get the first lady to the motorcade.

1012
01:34:27,158 --> 01:34:29,649
It's all right.

1013
01:34:29,761 --> 01:34:33,754
- Freeze!
- Password is Crystal.
Where'd Montrose take the president?

1014
01:34:33,865 --> 01:34:37,062
- Motorcade "B."
- Stay with me, ma'am.

1015
01:34:41,172 --> 01:34:43,231
This way.

1016
01:34:47,545 --> 01:34:51,072
- It's just this way, ma'am.
- Tom, where are we going?

1017
01:34:51,182 --> 01:34:54,174
We're going to motorcade "C," ma'am.

1018
01:34:58,056 --> 01:35:00,524
That's a hell of a way
to leave the G8.

1019
01:35:00,625 --> 01:35:04,459
<i>What is going on</i>
<i>with these goddamn radios?</i>

1020
01:35:12,537 --> 01:35:15,233
Go in twos.

1021
01:35:19,577 --> 01:35:23,240
What's next, boss?
What's the next move?

1022
01:35:23,347 --> 01:35:26,145
- <i>What's next?</i>
- Bill?

1023
01:35:26,250 --> 01:35:29,310
Hold the corridor.
Push 'em back.

1024
01:35:40,064 --> 01:35:42,396
Crystal!

1025
01:35:45,136 --> 01:35:48,731
<i>Pete, we're cut off</i>
<i>from the "B" motorcade.</i>

1026
01:36:13,631 --> 01:36:16,532
You okay?

1027
01:36:16,634 --> 01:36:18,534
- I think so.
- Turn off your locator.

1028
01:36:18,636 --> 01:36:20,627
What?

1029
01:36:20,738 --> 01:36:24,606
Your locator, turn it off. That's how
they know where we are. They're tracking us.

1030
01:36:24,709 --> 01:36:28,611
How do you...
How do you know?

1031
01:36:31,749 --> 01:36:35,378
Oh, no, Bill. Oh, God.

1032
01:36:54,405 --> 01:36:57,101
<i>Montrose was...</i>

1033
01:37:22,366 --> 01:37:25,233
<i>Pete. Pete.</i>

1034
01:37:25,336 --> 01:37:28,066
My family. My family. Pete!

1035
01:37:33,077 --> 01:37:35,545
Mr. President,
you're gonna have to trust us.

1036
01:37:35,646 --> 01:37:38,171
<i>We're gonna get you</i>
<i>up top to an evac car.</i>

1037
01:37:57,969 --> 01:38:00,995
Shooter's at 11:00.
I'll go high. You go low. You ready?

1038
01:38:01,105 --> 01:38:02,936
- Yeah.
- <i>Go.</i>

1039
01:38:12,216 --> 01:38:15,276
Get the president upstairs.
We'll cover you from here.

1040
01:38:31,936 --> 01:38:34,928
This way, ma'am.
As quick as you can.

1041
01:38:35,039 --> 01:38:37,564
Yes. Garrison.

1042
01:38:37,675 --> 01:38:40,610
<i>Need a hard car for</i>
<i>the president at southwest two.</i>

1043
01:38:40,711 --> 01:38:42,941
Coming to you, Pete.
Go. Go! Go, go!

1044
01:38:43,047 --> 01:38:45,447
<i>Southwest stairs.</i>
<i>Let's go get 'em!</i>

1045
01:38:45,549 --> 01:38:47,744
All right, we're gonna
get you out of here.

1046
01:39:41,138 --> 01:39:45,165
<i>Give me a perimeter</i>
<i>10 meters, 360 degrees!</i>

1047
01:39:58,989 --> 01:40:01,150
<i>President's hard car!</i>
<i>Let's get him in!</i>

1048
01:40:01,258 --> 01:40:05,058
Pete, I got him.
Mr. President, you're with me.

1049
01:40:23,381 --> 01:40:25,747
<i>The president is away!</i>

1050
01:40:32,556 --> 01:40:34,353
Go, go, go, go!

1051
01:40:38,229 --> 01:40:42,131
Oh, my God!
Oh, my God.

1052
01:40:47,571 --> 01:40:50,404
- <i>Secure the first lady!</i>
- <i>We need a hard car, now!</i>

1053
01:41:20,004 --> 01:41:22,063
Carl.

1054
01:41:22,173 --> 01:41:25,142
Listen, Pete, um...

1055
01:41:28,179 --> 01:41:30,079
You take care of yourself.

1056
01:41:32,550 --> 01:41:34,677
I'll save you a tee time.

1057
01:41:37,121 --> 01:41:39,988
Tom, you did a great job.
I was proud to work with you.

1058
01:41:40,090 --> 01:41:41,990
- Thanks.
- Thanks a lot.

1059
01:41:42,092 --> 01:41:45,425
I'll see you guys. Good careers.

1060
01:41:45,529 --> 01:41:48,054
Take care.

1061
01:41:48,165 --> 01:41:50,292
Do well, guys. See you soon.

1062
01:41:50,401 --> 01:41:53,336
- Hey, Pete.
- Yeah?

1063
01:41:54,705 --> 01:41:57,196
- This could be trouble.

1064
01:41:57,308 --> 01:42:01,972
- I'm gonna walk out of the
White House carrying this?

1065
01:42:02,079 --> 01:42:05,048
Thanks, guys.

1066
01:42:06,383 --> 01:42:09,045
- Bye-bye. All the best.
- <i>Hey, Pete!</i>

1067
01:42:09,153 --> 01:42:11,178
You gonna leave
without saying good-bye?

1068
01:42:11,288 --> 01:42:13,722
Well, look who's no longer a rookie.

1069
01:42:13,824 --> 01:42:15,815
Thanks.

1070
01:42:15,926 --> 01:42:18,019
So, how about
a little retirement dinner tonight?

1071
01:42:18,128 --> 01:42:20,892
I can't. I got a date.

1072
01:42:20,998 --> 01:42:24,331
- Something you want to tell me?
- With my wife.

1073
01:42:24,435 --> 01:42:26,528
That's great.

1074
01:42:26,637 --> 01:42:29,629
- Pete.
- See you around campus, Jill.

1075
01:42:29,740 --> 01:42:32,334
- Thanks for everything.
- Pleasure.

1076
01:42:35,346 --> 01:42:37,974
Yeah, I'm gonna miss it.

1077
01:42:38,082 --> 01:42:40,642
It's gonna miss you too.

1078
01:42:44,021 --> 01:42:46,819
Take care.

